{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Kspq8XRQM5weN6cLVdbcd","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 10.4: Model Resolution Module\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a model resolver that cascades task → agent → driver defaults,\n11\tso that the effective model for any task dispatch is deterministic and the workflow engine can resolve the correct model without hardcoding knowledge of the resolution chain.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new file `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts`\n16\t   **When** the file is inspected\n17\t   **Then** it exports a `resolveModel` function with signature `resolveModel(task: { model?: string }, agent: { model?: string }, driver: { defaultModel: string }) → string`\n18\t   **And** the function is a pure function with no side effects\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a task with `model: 'claude-opus-4-20250514'`, an agent with `model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`, and a driver with `defaultModel: 'claude-haiku-3-20250514'`\n22\t   **When** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` is called\n23\t   **Then** it returns `'claude-opus-4-20250514'` (task-level wins)\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** a task with no `model` field, an agent with `model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`, and a driver with `defaultModel: 'claude-haiku-3-20250514'`\n27\t   **When** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` is called\n28\t   **Then** it returns `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'` (agent-level fallback)\n29\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t4. **Given** a task with no `model` field, an agent with no `model` field, and a driver with `defaultModel: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`\n32\t   **When** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` is called\n33\t   **Then** it returns `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'` (driver default fallback)\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** a task with `model: undefined`, an agent with `model: undefined`, and a driver with `defaultModel: 'codex-mini'`\n37\t   **When** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` is called\n38\t   **Then** it returns `'codex-mini'`\n39\t   **And** this proves backward compatibility — existing workflows without model fields resolve to the driver default\n40\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n41\t\n42\t6. **Given** a task with `model: ''` (empty string), an agent with `model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`\n43\t   **When** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` is called\n44\t   **Then** the empty string is treated as \"not set\" and falls through to the agent model\n45\t   **And** the function returns `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`\n46\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t7. **Given** the `resolveModel` function\n49\t   **When** called with `driver.defaultModel` as an empty string\n50\t   **Then** it throws an error with a descriptive message indicating the driver has no default model\n51\t   **And** this is the only case where `resolveModel` throws\n52\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n53\t\n54\t8. **Given** the module `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts`\n55\t   **When** `src/lib/agents/index.ts` barrel is inspected\n56\t   **Then** `resolveModel` is re-exported from the barrel\n57\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n58\t\n59\t9. **Given** unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/model-resolver.test.ts`\n60\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n61\t   **Then** tests cover all 3 cascade levels (task wins, agent fallback, driver fallback)\n62\t   **And** tests cover edge cases: empty strings treated as unset, undefined fields, null fields\n63\t   **And** tests cover the driver-default-empty-string error case\n64\t   **And** tests verify the return type is `string`\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n68\t    **When** the build completes\n69\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n70\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n71\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n72\t\n73\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7)\n76\t  - [x] Implement `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` with 3-level cascade\n77\t  - [x] Treat empty strings as \"not set\" (fall through)\n78\t  - [x] Treat `null` and `undefined` as \"not set\" (fall through)\n79\t  - [x] Throw descriptive error if driver.defaultModel is empty/falsy (last resort must be valid)\n80\t  - [x] Export the function as a named export\n81\t\n82\t- [x] Task 2: Update barrel exports in `src/lib/agents/index.ts` (AC: #8)\n83\t  - [x] Re-export `resolveModel` from `./model-resolver.js`\n84\t\n85\t- [x] Task 3: Create unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/model-resolver.test.ts` (AC: #9, #10)\n86\t  - [x] Test: task model takes highest priority\n87\t  - [x] Test: agent model used when task has no model\n88\t  - [x] Test: driver default used when neither task nor agent specify one\n89\t  - [x] Test: empty string treated as unset at task level\n90\t  - [x] Test: empty string treated as unset at agent level\n91\t  - [x] Test: undefined fields fall through correctly\n92\t  - [x] Test: null fields fall through correctly\n93\t  - [x] Test: driver default empty string throws error\n94\t  - [x] Test: return type is always string\n95\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` succeeds\n96\t  - [x] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n97\t\n98\t## Dev Notes\n99\t\n100\t### Architecture Compliance\n101\t\n102\tThis story implements **Decision 4: Model Resolution** from `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md`. Key quote:\n103\t\n104\t> **Resolution order:**\n105\t> 1. Task-level `model` in workflow YAML (highest priority)\n106\t> 2. Agent-level `model` in agent YAML\n107\t> 3. Driver default model (hard-coded per driver)\n108\t>\n109\t> **Implementation:** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver) → task.model ?? agent.model ?? driver.defaultModel`\n110\t\n111\tThe architecture specifies a simple nullish coalescing chain. However, the implementation must also handle empty strings as \"not set\" because YAML parsers may produce `\"\"` for omitted fields, and this is a defensive best practice for config resolution.\n112\t\n113\t### Current State of the Codebase\n114\t\n115\t- **Agent configs (`ResolvedAgent` in `agent-resolver.ts`)** do NOT currently have a `model` field. The `SubagentDefinition` gets a hardcoded `DEFAULT_MODEL = 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'` in `compileSubagentDefinition()`. The model resolver does NOT modify `ResolvedAgent` — that will happen when the workflow schema is extended (story 11-1).\n116\t- **Workflow tasks** do NOT currently have a `model` field in `workflow.schema.json`. That will be added in story 11-1 (Workflow Schema Extension).\n117\t- **Driver `defaultModel`** is already defined on the `AgentDriver` interface (story 10-1) and implemented on `ClaudeCodeDriver` (story 10-3) as `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`.\n118\t\n119\tThe model resolver must accept loose input types (`{ model?: string }`) so it can work with both current configs (no model field) and future configs (model field added in stories 11-1+).\n120\t\n121\t### Input Type Design\n122\t\n123\tThe function parameters use structural typing (not imported interfaces) to avoid coupling to specific config shapes:\n124\t\n125\t```typescript\n126\texport function resolveModel(\n127\t  task: { model?: string | null },\n128\t  agent: { model?: string | null },\n129\t  driver: { defaultModel: string },\n130\t): string\n131\t```\n132\t\n133\tThis means any object with an optional `model` field works — `ResolvedAgent`, parsed workflow task, or a plain object in tests. The driver parameter requires `defaultModel` because every `AgentDriver` has it.\n134\t\n135\t### What NOT to Do\n136\t\n137\t- Do NOT modify `agent-resolver.ts` — agent model field comes later (story 11-1)\n138\t- Do NOT modify `workflow.schema.json` — task model/driver fields come later (story 11-1)\n139\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` — integration comes in story 10-5\n140\t- Do NOT modify `ClaudeCodeDriver` or `factory.ts` — they are already done\n141\t- Do NOT add a `model` field to `ResolvedAgent` — that's story 11-1's job\n142\t\n143\t### Driver Default Models (for reference)\n144\t\n145\tFrom the architecture document:\n146\t- `claude-code`: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`\n147\t- `codex`: `codex-mini`\n148\t- `opencode`: inherits from OpenCode's own config\n149\t\n150\t### Testing Patterns\n151\t\n152\t- Follow existing Vitest patterns in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/`\n153\t- Pure function tests — no mocking needed, no async, no filesystem\n154\t- Use `describe/it/expect` structure\n155\t- Each cascade level gets its own test case\n156\t- Edge cases (empty string, null, undefined) get explicit tests\n157\t\n158\t### References\n159\t\n160\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 4: Model Resolution]\n161\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 1.4: Model Resolution Module]\n162\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — AgentDriver.defaultModel]\n163\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts — ClaudeCodeDriver.defaultModel]\n164\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — current DEFAULT_MODEL hardcoding]\n165\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LRGwVdnBi8B25YdHRso3f2","session_id":"2c102368-34ec-49f5-8d34-59f136ae42aa","uuid":"a9b48203-5356-4f1e-9692-50de61943e53","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:25:13.762Z"}
