{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJNMpNVY3jk9U1Lf7JcSsJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * Model Resolution Module (Story 10-4).\n3\t *\n4\t * Resolves the effective model for a task dispatch using a 3-level cascade:\n5\t *   1. Task-level model (highest priority)\n6\t *   2. Agent-level model\n7\t *   3. Driver default model (lowest priority, must be valid)\n8\t *\n9\t * Architecture reference: Decision 4 in architecture-multi-framework.md.\n10\t */\n11\t\n12\t/**\n13\t * Resolves the effective model string using a task → agent → driver cascade.\n14\t *\n15\t * Empty strings, `null`, and `undefined` are all treated as \"not set\" and\n16\t * fall through to the next level. The driver's `defaultModel` is the final\n17\t * fallback and must be a non-empty string — if it is falsy, an error is thrown.\n18\t *\n19\t * @param task   - Object with an optional `model` field (e.g. workflow task)\n20\t * @param agent  - Object with an optional `model` field (e.g. resolved agent config)\n21\t * @param driver - Object with a required `defaultModel` field (e.g. AgentDriver)\n22\t * @returns The resolved model string\n23\t * @throws {Error} If `driver.defaultModel` is empty or falsy\n24\t */\n25\texport function resolveModel(\n26\t  task: { model?: string | null },\n27\t  agent: { model?: string | null },\n28\t  driver: { defaultModel: string },\n29\t): string {\n30\t  if (!driver.defaultModel) {\n31\t    throw new Error(\n32\t      'Driver has no default model: driver.defaultModel must be a non-empty string',\n33\t    );\n34\t  }\n35\t\n36\t  if (task.model) {\n37\t    return task.model;\n38\t  }\n39\t\n40\t  if (agent.model) {\n41\t    return agent.model;\n42\t  }\n43\t\n44\t  return driver.defaultModel;\n45\t}\n46\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LRGwVdnBi8B25YdHRso3f2","session_id":"2c102368-34ec-49f5-8d34-59f136ae42aa","uuid":"44036ea6-7815-4f32-b617-f9b9e75c6dec","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:25:18.537Z"}
