{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LRGwVdnBi8B25YdHRso3f2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. The implementation is correct.\n\n---\n\n**Code Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** 10-4-model-resolution-module.md\n**Status:** verifying\n\n**Issues Found:** 1 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 2 LOW\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM (all HIGH and MEDIUM fixed)\n\n**Changes made:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts` — Fixed driver validation to only fire when actually falling through to driver default (architecture compliance). Added whitespace trimming for model strings.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/__tests__/model-resolver.test.ts` — Fixed incorrect test asserting wrong throw behavior. Added 6 new tests: whitespace-only strings at task/agent/both levels, whitespace-only driver default throws, model string trimming, agent-with-empty-driver-no-throw.\n\n**Coverage:** 96.73% overall, all 167 files above 80% floor. 164 test files, 4308 tests, zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- **HIGH**: Driver validation fired unconditionally before cascade resolution, violating architecture Decision 4's nullish-coalescing semantics. A valid task-level model + empty driver.defaultModel would throw instead of returning the task model. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: Whitespace-only model strings (`\"  \"`) passed through as valid model names instead of being treated as \"not set\". Could cause downstream dispatch failures with invisible model names. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: Test on line 129-135 asserted the wrong behavior (expected throw when task has valid model + empty driver default) and documented it as correct with a misleading comment. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- No Dev Agent Record / File List section in story file — story lacks traceability metadata expected by the review workflow.\n- Story file and new source files are untracked in git (not staged) — this is expected since commit was not requested.\n- The `@throws` JSDoc line still says \"If `driver.defaultModel` is empty or falsy\" without clarifying \"and no task/agent model resolves first\" — minor doc inconsistency.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. model-resolver.ts has 100% line/branch/function coverage. All 167 project files above 80% floor.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `trim()` behavior means `resolveModel` returns trimmed model strings, while the driver's `defaultModel` is returned untrimmed (line 50 returns `driver.defaultModel` raw). This is a minor asymmetry — if a driver has a defaultModel with trailing whitespace, it would be returned as-is. Acceptable for now since drivers are class instances with hardcoded const strings.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this session.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 5, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~20 lines), `npx codeharness coverage` (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 6 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — coverage command run twice (before and after fixes, both necessary)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2746ed082bd1066e (use SendMessage with to: 'a2746ed082bd1066e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44963\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 208668</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c102368-34ec-49f5-8d34-59f136ae42aa","uuid":"86f4f274-ba14-4d80-a201-bbd0d52d8e95","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:28:33.211Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-4-model-resolution-module.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure a